Vagrant commands:

1. vagrant init nameofos - Create file vagrantfile which contains all the configurationn related to the OS
2. vagrant up - start the VM
3. vagrant halt - Stop the VM
4. vagrant destroy - Remove the OS
5. Vagrant ssh - log in to the VM (password- vagrant)
6. Vagrant suspend - pause the VM and save the state
7. Vagrant resume - resume the VM
8. vagrant reload - shutdown and restart the VM
9. vagrant box list - list of boxes present in the local



-- Adding user

useradd username
passwd username

enter the password



-- disk size

fdisk -l



Change authentication in /etc/ssh/sshd_config file

change passwordauthentication to yes

service ssh restart


